(105, 'lajkau', 'I am a psychologist who has been a volunteer counselor for the Pregnancy Loss Support Program in NYC for over 20 years and am on their Board of Advisors. I also experienced a late term stillbirth, miscarriage, and secondary infertility myself. I am joining this community in response to a request from Melanie Cashman. \r\nSo far, the site looks great. I like the photo of the reeds blowing in the wind, which signifies, I think, how individuals and couples feel after their loss. I also think the Thoughts for Friends and Family will be helpful to many, as so many people with whom I have worked have been on the receiving end of comments that, while often unintended, have been quite hurtful.\r\nGood luck as you continue to develop this site.', 38, 14, '2010-06-13 15:28:02');
