(19, 3, '2010-04-22 15:00:31', '2010-04-22 15:00:31', 'I''m in the moment of the ultrasound without a heartbeat. I knew the second they put the wand on my stomach- I knew he was gone. All else- the cheery technician telling me to look at my son''s profile, the call to the doctor to look for herself, the silence in my hospital room, the ''I''m sorry'', all of it was distant, was like watching a movie. Like watching the cloud of dust after the towers fell here in NYC.\r\n\r\nSome people know that moment only from the movies. (lucky for them). There wasn''t weeping or loud cries of NO like actors do. There is just an earth shattering silence thickly encased in shock. I have no idea if there were actually any tears.\r\n\r\nUntil today. I found myself back in that moment. I cried for that moment- Tiger''s moment. I heard myself say NO, I saw my hands shaking, I felt my chest vibrating.\r\n\r\nAnd I wanted what you might think I would have asked for that day but didn''t until this morning: I wanted to go back- I wanted to go back to the day before Tiger died and I wanted to save him. I know. But that''s what I wanted. Just my super-mom costume and the power of time travel.\r\n\r\n"Have you ever thought about what protects our hearts?\r\nJust a cage of rib bones and other various parts\r\nSo it''s fairly simple to cut right through the mess,\r\nAnd to stop the muscle that makes us confess\r\n\r\nAnd we are so fragile,\r\nAnd our cracking bones make noise,\r\nAnd we are just,\r\nBreakable, breakable, breakable girls and boys" - Ingrid Michaelson', 'Breaking through the shock ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'breaking-through-the-shock', '', '', '2010-12-22 10:57:36', '2010-12-22 10:57:36', '', 0, 'http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/?p=19', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(20, 3, '2010-04-22 14:57:09', '2010-04-22 14:57:09', 'I''m in the moment of the ultrasound without a heartbeat. I knew the second they put the wand on my stomach- I knew he was gone. All else- the cheery technician telling me to look at my son''s profile, the call of the doctor to look, the silence in my hospital room, the ''I''m sorry'', all of it was distant, was like watching a movie. Like watching the cloud of dust after the towers fell here in NYC.\n\nSome people only know that moment from the movies. There wasn''t weeping or loud cries of NO like actors do. There is just an earth shattering silence thickly encased in shock. I have no idea if there were actually any tears.\n\nUntil today. I found myself back in that moment. I cried for that moment- Tiger''s moment. I heard myself say NO, I saw my hand shaking, I felt my chest vibrating.\n\nAnd I wanted what you might think I would have asked for that day but didn''t until this morning: I wanted to go back- I wanted to go back to the day before Tiger died and I wanted to save him. I know. But that''s what I wanted.\n\n"\n\nHave you ever thought about what protects our hearts?\nJust a cage of rib bones and other various parts\nSo it''s fairly simple to cut right through the mess,\nAnd to stop the muscle that makes us confess\n\nAnd we are so fragile,\nAnd our cracking bones make noise,\nAnd we are just,\nBreakable, breakable, breakable girls and boys" - Ingrid Michaelson', 'Breaking through the shock ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '19-revision', '', '', '2010-04-22 14:57:09', '2010-04-22 14:57:09', '', 19, 'http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2010/04/22/19-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
