(22, 3, '2010-04-22 16:03:49', '2010-04-22 16:03:49', 'I think we should start where I can for now:\r\n\r\nSome time after Tiger died- maybe a month, maybe two- Tom and I sat on the steps of our backyard deck. We talked with some strangely inspired clarity about our two boys. We knew Will was strong and gentle. That he would be solid  and true with a sharp sense of humor. He was very different than his sister and would have loved her deeply from a distance. He would always have gone the extra mile. But taken risks. His love would be quiet and complete. Tiger, he was all fire. He was passionate and sneaky. He would have been trouble and would have broken hearts. We would not have held our breath at his risky ways. He would have loved fiercely.  Maybe it was in the names. Maybe. But I don''t think so.\r\n\r\nHere''s what happened...', 'Our Story', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '13-autosave', '', '', '2010-04-22 16:03:49', '2010-04-22 16:03:49', '', 13, 'http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2010/04/22/13-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
