(243, '_transient_dash_aa95765b5cc111c56d5993d476b1c2f0', '<div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/yTu1OnCLKyY/'' title=''Are you looking for a super-simple quick reference for WP_Query and all of its parameters? Loosely described, WP_Query is how WordPress displays posts defined by a variety of parameters, and keeping that of the available parameters can be a monumental task. It’s easy to forget all that you can do with WP_Query if you aren’t working with it every single day.  [&hellip;]''>Weblog Tools Collection: WP_Query Quick Reference</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~3/MEy40vJPxpo/congrats-to-jane-wells'' title=''As I mentioned about a month ago, Jane Wells has been working on a new venture called Jitterbug which aims to be a bakery with a cafe feel complete with WiFi. To help fund this venture and to purchase some equipment, Jane put together a project on KickStarter.com to generate crowd sourced capital. The monetary goal was $15,000.00 and that was reached just 4  [&hellip;]''>WPTavern: Congrats To Jane Wells</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wordpress.tv/2012/03/13/wordcamp-phoenix-2012-opening-remarks/'' title='' [&hellip;]''>WordPress.tv: WordCamp Phoenix 2012: Opening Remarks</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wordpress.tv/2012/03/12/julio-potier-wordpress-et-la-securite-des-extensions/'' title='' [&hellip;]''>WordPress.tv: Julio Potier : WordPress et la sécurité des extensions</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wordpress.tv/2012/03/12/greg-taylor-wordpress-for-musicians-artists-writers-butchers-bakers-candlestick-makers/'' title='' [&hellip;]''>WordPress.tv: Greg Taylor: WordPress for Musicians, Artists, Writers, Butchers, Bakers &amp; Candlestick Makers</a></li></ul></div>', 'no'),
