(82, 2, 'activity', 'activity_update', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/tombrennan/" title="tombrennan">tombrennan</a> posted an update:', 'A lot of work on the site today in terms of creating users and adding them to Groups. Feels good.', 'http://hopeinloss.org/members/tombrennan/', 0, 0, '2010-06-16 23:09:00', 0, 0, 0, 0),
(83, 10, 'groups', 'new_forum_post', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/giorgianabiazzo/" title="Ganna">Ganna</a> posted on the forum topic <a href="http://hopeinloss.org/groups/mothers/forum/topic/how-old-he-would-be-today">How old he would be today </a> in the group <a href="http://hopeinloss.org/groups/mothers/">Mothers  (Members)</a>:', 'Teo would have been 6, just about 6 and a half, but how I think of him is a bit of a contradiction. On the one hand, he will always be a baby. He is my forever baby suspended in time. Then on the other hand, he is 6. As the years have passed I [...]', 'http://hopeinloss.org/groups/mothers/forum/topic/how-old-he-would-be-today/#post-6', 1, 6, '2010-06-18 00:38:26', 1, 0, 0, 0),
(84, 3, 'blogs', 'new_blog_post', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/susanbrennan/" title="susanbrennan">susanbrennan</a> wrote a new blog post: <a href="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2010/06/22/where-do-we-go-from-here-my-love-where-will-we-be-tomorrow/">Where do we go from here my love? Where will we be tomorrow? </a>', '<img src="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/files/2010/06/IMG_0513-300x225.jpg" width="133.33333333333" height="100" alt="Thumbnail" class="align-left thumbnail" />I don''t want to grieve forever. I don''t want to wish forever. I''m trying to parse the difference between honoring and grieving. It''s work- lovingly remembering and creatively honoring a dream. More often than not I need that work and dive in: I find it healing. It takes me back to that powerful world after Tiger [...]', 'http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2010/06/22/where-do-we-go-from-here-my-love-where-will-we-be-tomorrow/', 2, 90, '2010-06-22 14:19:25', 0, 0, 0, 0),
(85, 5, 'groups', 'new_forum_post', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/liisa/" title="liisa">liisa</a> posted on the forum topic <a href="http://hopeinloss.org/groups/mothers/forum/topic/how-old-he-would-be-today">How old he would be today </a> in the group <a href="http://hopeinloss.org/groups/mothers/">Mothers  (Members)</a>:', 'Basil would be just over 14 months. All the wondering about ''what he would be doing now'' is both healing and torturous. On one hand, I''ll never really know when he would have learned to talk or walk; but on the other hand, all those thoughts continue to validate Basil''s humannes. He really did exhist--physically, [...]', 'http://hopeinloss.org/groups/mothers/forum/topic/how-old-he-would-be-today/#post-7', 1, 7, '2010-06-24 17:35:51', 1, 0, 0, 0),
(87, 3, 'groups', 'new_forum_post', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/susanbrennan/" title="susanbrennan">susanbrennan</a> posted on the forum topic <a href="http://hopeinloss.org/groups/mothers/forum/topic/how-old-he-would-be-today/">How old he would be today </a> in the group <a href="http://hopeinloss.org/groups/mothers/">Mothers  (Members)</a>:', 'I also think about the alternate world where my boys live Liisa (do all of us?)... the one where everything went fine and they are their age. Just yesterday this 4 1/2 year old boy joined us randomly in the park. His name was Oscar (Will''s name is Will because he was born early and [...]', 'http://hopeinloss.org/groups/mothers/forum/topic/how-old-he-would-be-today/#post-8', 1, 8, '2010-06-28 17:29:47', 1, 0, 0, 0),
(88, 3, 'groups', 'new_forum_topic', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/susanbrennan/" title="susanbrennan">susanbrennan</a> started the forum topic <a href="http://hopeinloss.org/groups/everyone/forum/topic/feedback-for-thoughts-for-friends-and-family/">Feedback for Thoughts for Friends and Family</a> in the group <a href="http://hopeinloss.org/groups/everyone/">Everyone  (Members)</a>:', 'Hello everyone. I wrote a draft of ''Thoughts for Friends and Family'' before we even met. I would love feedback so that I can incorporate your input and ask Melanie to edit it. It is one of the PAGES to the right here. If you have time to read it and add/comment/subtract please do that [...]', 'http://hopeinloss.org/groups/everyone/forum/topic/feedback-for-thoughts-for-friends-and-family/', 3, 5, '2010-06-29 13:45:44', 1, 0, 0, 0),
(89, 2, 'groups', 'joined_group', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/tombrennan/" title="tombrennan">tombrennan</a> joined the group <a href="http://hopeinloss.org/groups/public-everyone/">Public Everyone</a>', '', 'http://hopeinloss.org/members/tombrennan/', 4, 0, '2010-07-01 14:45:00', 0, 0, 0, 0),
(92, 2, 'groups', 'new_forum_topic', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/tombrennan/" title="tombrennan">tombrennan</a> started the forum topic <a href="http://hopeinloss.org/groups/public-everyone/forum/topic/on-the-struggle-between-dwelling-on-the-past-and-healthy-grieving/">On the struggle between dwelling on the past and healthy grieving.</a> in the group <a href="http://hopeinloss.org/groups/public-everyone/">Public Everyone</a>:', 'I''m nearing the end of Elizabeth McCracken''s wonderful, An Exact Replica of a Figment of My Imagination. It''s about her journey through the loss of her son, Pudding. But this topic and this post are not about the book. It''s about how reading the book made me feel. Wistful, sad, guilty, hopeful -- sometimes a [...]', 'http://hopeinloss.org/groups/public-everyone/forum/topic/on-the-struggle-between-dwelling-on-the-past-and-healthy-grieving/', 4, 6, '2010-07-01 14:51:49', 0, 0, 0, 0),
(93, 3, 'blogs', 'new_blog_post', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/susanbrennan/" title="susanbrennan">susanbrennan</a> wrote a new blog post: <a href="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2010/07/02/a-reversal-a-surprise-a-country-and-western-twang/">A reversal? A surprise. A country and western twang.</a>', '<img src="//1F5A374B-5AA8-4BFD-AF1C-ADDBBDD7C236/image.tiff" width="100" height="100" alt="Thumbnail" class="align-left thumbnail" />So I''ve added boys to the mix of babies I''ve held. In all its complication it was delightful. I so love babies. And their moms and the infant eyes looking up at you and their heads on your shoulder. Its a good reminder... remember...there <em>can</em> be joy. Each child is it''s own universe. I can enjoy them [...]', 'http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2010/07/02/a-reversal-a-surprise-a-country-and-western-twang/', 2, 96, '2010-07-02 16:13:25', 0, 0, 0, 0),
(94, 3, 'blogs', 'new_blog_post', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/susanbrennan/" title="susanbrennan">susanbrennan</a> wrote a new blog post: <a href="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2010/07/13/superstitious/">Superstitious </a>', '<img src="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/files/2010/07/images.jpeg" width="101.6" height="100" alt="Thumbnail" class="align-left thumbnail" /><em><a href="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/files/2010/07/images.jpeg"></a></em> <div> <em>Around 18-24 months the bereaved begin to move on... to get organized, start enjoying themselves and stop feeling guilty about this positive feeling. </em> It''s 13 months. It''s the 13th of July. Will died on February 13th. Tiger died on June 13th. I posted on Glow today- it was the 13th response. I feel very 13- odd, [...]</div>', 'http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2010/07/13/superstitious/', 2, 110, '2010-07-13 17:01:08', 0, 0, 0, 0),
(95, 5, 'groups', 'joined_group', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/liisa/" title="liisa">liisa</a> joined the group <a href="http://hopeinloss.org/groups/public-everyone/">Public Everyone</a>', '', 'http://hopeinloss.org/members/liisa/', 4, 0, '2010-07-13 17:49:40', 0, 0, 0, 0),
(96, 5, 'groups', 'new_forum_post', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/liisa/" title="liisa">liisa</a> posted on the forum topic <a href="http://hopeinloss.org/groups/public-everyone/forum/topic/on-the-struggle-between-dwelling-on-the-past-and-healthy-grieving">On the struggle between dwelling on the past and healthy grieving.</a> in the group <a href="http://hopeinloss.org/groups/public-everyone/">Public Everyone</a>:', 'Oh geez, I can so relate. Elizabeth McCracken''s book was my favorite on the topic (It sounds dark to have a ''favorite'' babydying book, but after the dozens I''ve read, I have earned the right to have a favorite). Several of her chapters were read while at a 4th of July BBQ last year. One [...]', 'http://hopeinloss.org/groups/public-everyone/forum/topic/on-the-struggle-between-dwelling-on-the-past-and-healthy-grieving/#post-11', 4, 11, '2010-07-13 17:49:40', 0, 0, 0, 0),
(97, 3, 'groups', 'new_forum_post', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/susanbrennan/" title="susanbrennan">susanbrennan</a> posted on the forum topic <a href="http://hopeinloss.org/groups/public-everyone/forum/topic/on-the-struggle-between-dwelling-on-the-past-and-healthy-grieving/">On the struggle between dwelling on the past and healthy grieving.</a> in the group <a href="http://hopeinloss.org/groups/public-everyone/">Public Everyone</a>:', 'I feel so sad- not so much THAT a woman is pregnant- I''m saddest about the fact that I don''t feel that happiness at the wonder of it all, when I see that belly, anymore. And I get really stuck there. I''m thrown back to being pregnant one second, then I am the woman who [...]', 'http://hopeinloss.org/groups/public-everyone/forum/topic/on-the-struggle-between-dwelling-on-the-past-and-healthy-grieving/#post-12', 4, 12, '2010-07-14 18:23:31', 0, 0, 0, 0),
(98, 3, 'groups', 'new_forum_topic', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/susanbrennan/" title="susanbrennan">susanbrennan</a> started the forum topic <a href="http://hopeinloss.org/groups/mothers/forum/topic/body-memory-2/">body memory </a> in the group <a href="http://hopeinloss.org/groups/mothers/">Mothers  (Members)</a>:', 'The ebb and flow of sadness always takes me by surprise. I''m more grounded, compassionate, I laugh and am really dealing with the world here without my boys and then something reminds me..... and I''m back. Maybe not all the way back but to that place.... and it seems to happen in a moment. And [...]', 'http://hopeinloss.org/groups/mothers/forum/topic/body-memory-2/', 1, 9, '2010-07-14 18:26:49', 1, 0, 0, 0),
(99, 2, 'activity', 'activity_update', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/tombrennan/" title="tombrennan">tombrennan</a> posted an update:', 'wondering why I feel like such an idiot all the time. ', 'http://hopeinloss.org/members/tombrennan/', 0, 0, '2010-07-15 01:19:56', 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_bp_activity` (`id`, `user_id`, `component`, `type`, `action`, `content`, `primary_link`, `item_id`, `secondary_item_id`, `date_recorded`, `hide_sitewide`, `mptt_left`, `mptt_right`, `is_spam`) VALUES
(102, 3, 'blogs', 'new_blog_post', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/susanbrennan/" title="susanbrennan">susanbrennan</a> wrote a new blog post: <a href="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2010/03/09/my-two-cents-to-babyloss-moms-on-the-death-preoccupation-glow/">my two cents to babyloss moms on the death-preoccupation (glow)</a>', '<img src="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/files/2010/11/Fear-Of-Flying-Remixes-Volume-1-300x300.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Thumbnail" class="align-left thumbnail" />One of my biggest struggles after losing Will and again after losing Tiger: My 5 year old daughter. It is not new but it has that raw experienced-based-fear attached to it when it comes. I couldn''t fly after Will died for months. A panic took me over once I did fly- just wrapped its icy fingers [...]', 'http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2010/03/09/my-two-cents-to-babyloss-moms-on-the-death-preoccupation-glow/', 2, 127, '2010-03-09 22:34:31', 0, 0, 0, 0),
(103, 3, 'blogs', 'new_blog_post', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/susanbrennan/" title="susanbrennan">susanbrennan</a> wrote a new blog post: <a href="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2010/11/29/same-love-different-life-repost-from-glow/">Same Love, Different Life (repost from Glow)</a>', '<img src="http://hopeinloss.org/files/2010/11/IMG_2055-225x300.jpg" width="75" height="100" alt="Thumbnail" class="align-left thumbnail" />It wasn''t so bad really- no one remembers, or should I say, no one takes the chance to say anything anymore. A year and a half? They would be embarrassed or find their inquiry inappropriate so after the fact. But did he cross their minds when they saw me? Did they feel anything? This was mostly [...]', 'http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2010/11/29/same-love-different-life-repost-from-glow/', 2, 132, '2010-11-29 11:25:13', 0, 0, 0, 0),
(106, 3, 'blogs', 'new_blog_post', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/susanbrennan/" title="susanbrennan">susanbrennan</a> wrote a new blog post: <a href="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2011/01/21/back-to-the-space-between/">Back to the space between</a>', '<img src="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/files/2011/01/images.jpeg" width="76.953125" height="100" alt="Thumbnail" class="align-left thumbnail" />I found something that I had a written after Tiger died but had since forgotten about. So it must have been in November of 2009. I was super into transforming and sculpting the immediate raw grief after we lost Tiger. After Will it was just complete shock... which informed me the second time. I have a [...]', 'http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2011/01/21/back-to-the-space-between/', 2, 156, '2011-01-21 19:15:23', 0, 0, 0, 0),
(107, 3, 'blogs', 'new_blog_post', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/susanbrennan/" title="susanbrennan">susanbrennan</a> wrote a new blog post: <a href="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2011/02/02/i-wonder-about-him/">I wonder about him</a>', 'Will''s birthday is coming up. His 5th. The anniversary of his death too- his 5th. I can''t wrap my brain around time. When I feel better about the boys- like my grief has been worked through and I''m generally happy- I have this small feeling of missing the mourning. Weird. But there is guilt attached [...]', 'http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2011/02/02/i-wonder-about-him/', 2, 161, '2011-02-02 18:53:17', 0, 0, 0, 0),
(108, 3, 'blogs', 'new_blog_post', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/susanbrennan/" title="susanbrennan">susanbrennan</a> wrote a new blog post: <a href="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2012/02/10/6-years-less-poetic-more-integrated-just-like-yesterday/">6 years: less poetic, more integrated, just like yesterday</a>', '<img src="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/files/2012/02/images.jpeg" width="158.59375" height="100" alt="Thumbnail" class="align-left thumbnail" /><a href="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/files/2012/02/images.jpeg"></a>A year since my last post: a testament to healing and life happening and new intensities taking up space. I was out with two of my favorite and oldest friends in ''Brooklyn: the modern Paris of the 30s'' at a tapas bar to celebrate my birthday. My sweet Amy acknowledged Will''s name on her calendar. She [...]', 'http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2012/02/10/6-years-less-poetic-more-integrated-just-like-yesterday/', 2, 168, '2012-02-10 15:55:58', 0, 0, 0, 0),
(109, 3, 'blogs', 'new_blog_post', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/susanbrennan/" title="susanbrennan">susanbrennan</a> wrote a new post, <a href="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2012/07/08/177/"></a>, on the site <a href="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org">A Walk in the Park</a>', '<a href="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2012/07/08/177/"><img src="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/files/2012/07/Brave-mother-and-daughter-wild-300x225.jpg" width="133.33333333333" height="100" alt="Thumbnail" class="align-left thumbnail" /></a><em>“It''s so curious: one can resist tears and ''behave'' very well in the hardest hours of grief. But then someone makes you a friendly sign behind a window, or one notices that a flower that was in bud only yesterday [&hellip;]</em>', 'http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2012/07/08/177/', 2, 177, '2012-07-08 18:34:58', 0, 0, 0, 0),
(111, 3, 'blogs', 'new_blog_post', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/susanbrennan/" title="susanbrennan">susanbrennan</a> wrote a new post, <a href="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2013/02/12/slides-or-swings/">Slides or Swings</a>, on the site <a href="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org">A Walk in the Park</a>', '<a href="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2013/02/12/slides-or-swings/"><img src="//32DCC812-A58D-419F-8BD6-597C5C274C9F/imgres.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Thumbnail" class="align-left thumbnail" /></a><a href="//32DCC812-A58D-419F-8BD6-597C5C274C9F/imgres.jpg"></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI have the flu. I walked out with Tom and Lucy and Fletcher this morning for the first time in three days. Dropped off Lucy at school. Walked to Will''s tree. Feeling too sick, I left Tom and Fletch to [&hellip;]', 'http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2013/02/12/slides-or-swings/', 2, 186, '2013-02-14 01:47:21', 0, 0, 0, 0),
(112, 3, 'blogs', 'new_blog_post', '<a href="http://hopeinloss.org/members/susanbrennan/" title="susanbrennan">susanbrennan</a> wrote a new post, <a href="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2013/05/17/my-calendar/">My Calendar</a>, on the site <a href="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org">A Walk in the Park</a>', '<a href="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2013/05/17/my-calendar/"><img src="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/files/2013/05/images.jpeg" width="129.94923857868" height="100" alt="Thumbnail" class="align-left thumbnail" /></a><a href="http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/?attachment_id=203" rel="attachment wp-att-203"></a>These are my dates that never change.... most of which few but me know anymore or remember. They remain my touch stones .... at times for rest and focus and others? I slam into them just when I was catching the [&hellip;]', 'http://susantomwillandtiger.hopeinloss.org/2013/05/17/my-calendar/', 2, 201, '2013-05-17 15:24:16', 0, 0, 0, 0);
